ogical and convincing. However, if someone is dismissive or imposes their views, you won’t waste your time.</li>\r\n<li>Deep down, you want to share your knowledge meaningfully and make a real impact.</li>\r\n<li>You also have a strong internal drive to stand out in terms of intelligence and understanding. This might manifest overtly or subtly, depending on the individual.</li>\r\n<li>In addition to being wise, you possess strong intuition—be it gut feelings, empathy, spiritual perception, or a psychic connection.</li>\r\n<li>You have a powerful ability to synthesize knowledge and draw lessons from everyday moments like falling leaves, stars in the sky, or flowing water. This contributes to your ever-growing wisdom.</li>\r\n<li>Though often quiet, you are among the most active and curious people internally. You constantly seek new personal experiences, whether or not you realize it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 id="your-weaknesses">YOUR WEAKNESSES</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You admire only those who surpass you intellectually. You tend to trust your own perspectives and dislike others’ rules—though ironically, you may try to impose your own rules on others.</li>\r\n<li>People often find you hard to understand. You rarely open up fully, either because you believe others won&#39;t understand you or because you don&#39;t want them to.</li>\r\n<li>At times, you appear detached or indifferent. You may be lost in thought—or feel completely empty. Others see you as deeply contemplative.</li>\r\n<li>You&#39;re emotionally unpredictable. When inspired, you&#39;re focused and even perfectionistic. When uninspired, you&#39;re sluggish and irritated by pressure. Your mood can switch from cold and withdrawn to childlike joy.</li>\r\n<li>You are prone to stress or nervous exhaustion, especially when exposed to loud noises, criticism, or judgment. While usually temporary, repeated exposure can lead to more serious emotional imbalance.</li>\r\n<li>Because you crave firsthand learning, you&#39;re 