ll, thought is one of your greatest strengths.</li>\r\n<li>Intelligence is one of your finest traits, but beware its darker side. Excessive arrogance can push friendships away and leave you isolated. Sometimes, knowing too many logical facts can make you skeptical and hard to reach.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Your Capacity to Learn</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You thrive on logic. To you, everything must make sense. Truth is truth. Mysticism, mysteries, psychics—many may not believe in these, but you may have a natural intuitive gift when it comes to spirituality.</li>\r\n<li>Your destiny involves helping others—as a leader, a teacher, a healer, or someone supporting the ill and disabled. And if you work through your spiritual abilities, you can use them to help, to guide, to inspire…</li>\r\n<li>But always speak the truth! You may be tempted to comfort others by saying things you haven’t fully verified, expressed in convincing logic. But deceiving those you aim to help—even unintentionally—is not right.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Your Insight</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>You are deeply insightful. Not only from practical study, but you carry a natural wisdom and intelligence. Your life experience gives you the sense that everything can be learned and mastered.</li>\r\n<li>Yet your greatest challenge may lie in the internal tension between two of your traits: intellect and the ability to learn. It can be hard to balance both in your mind. When you come across as a heavy debater, you may begin doubting yourself due to your high inner standards—and that’s understandable.</li>\r\n<li>But you know your experience, and you don’t lie. Don’t let doubt hold you back. Allow yourself to step into the unknown. The universe is strange and vast, and it gave you the gift of learning for a reason.</li>\r\n</ul>
